    <h1 class="title">Tips for Success</h1>
  </div>

  <div class="tip">
    <div class="tip-number">1</div>
    <div class="tip-content">
      <div class="tip-title">Be Consistent</div>
      <p>Use the same sign every time for each word. Sign during daily routines - meals, diaper changes, bath time.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="tip">
    <div class="tip-number">2</div>
    <div class="tip-content">
      <div class="tip-title">Say the Word</div>
      <p>Always say the word OUT LOUD while signing. This helps with speech development and reinforces the connection.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="tip">
    <div class="tip-number">3</div>
    <div class="tip-content">
      <div class="tip-title">Start Simple</div>
      <p>Begin with 3-5 signs that are most useful: MILK, MORE, EAT, ALL DONE. Add new signs once baby masters these.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="tip">
    <div class="tip-number">4</div>
    <div class="tip-content">
      <div class="tip-title">Make Eye Contact</div>
      <p>Get baby's attention before signing. Sign within their line of sight so they can see both the sign and the
        object.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="tip">
    <div class="tip-number">5</div>
    <div class="tip-content">
      <div class="tip-title">Be Patient</div>
      <p>It may take weeks or months before baby signs back. Keep signing! They're absorbing everything you show them.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="tip">
    <div class="tip-number">6</div>
    <div class="tip-content">
      <div class="tip-title">Celebrate Attempts</div>
      <p>Any approximation of a sign counts! Even if it's not perfect, respond enthusiastically to encourage more
        communication.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="tip">
    <div class="tip-number">7</div>
    <div class="tip-content">
      <div class="tip-title">Get Everyone Involved</div>
      <p>Teach signs to caregivers, grandparents, and siblings. The more people who sign with baby, the faster they'll
        learn.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

